The paper describes a new algorithm for exploring search spaces to find high-performing solutions, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of neural networks and soft robots in the examples suggests that the paper may be relevant to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on exploring the relationship between performance and dimensions of interest in solutions suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE) and systems and control (cs.SY).
